                <p class="faq_q">Q1. How do I redeem the gifts here?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">You need to sign up a member first.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q2. Do I have to pay for the membership?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">No. The membership is free.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q3. What do I have to purchase to redeem the free gifts?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">You have to purchase any books published by Marshall Cavendish Education to earn you points for redemption. This is applicable only for purchases made in Singapore.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q4. How do I earn the points required to redeem the free gifts?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">Every $1.00 spent on Marshall Cavendish Education books entitles you to 1 point. You can accumulate the points to redeem the gifts of your choice.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q5. Is there a validity period for the points earned?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">Yes. All points are valid for 12 months from date of issue.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q6. How do I submit the invoice to earn the points?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">You can take a clear photo of the invoice/receipt indicating the purchase of your Marshall Cavendish Education books. Submit the photo via via your MC EduPerks account.</a></p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q7. How do I know if the submission is successful?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">An acknowledgement email will be sent to you once we received the entry.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q8. How do I know if the points are awarded after the submission?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">Our customer service officer will validate your entry and award the points according to the total amount spent on the qualified items. An email will be sent to you within 3 working days once the points are awarded. All awarded points and redemption records will be listed on your 'Member's Area' page when you log in.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q9. What do I need to present to collect the free gifts ?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">All collection details will be provided in the notification to your email. Members are required to present the email over the counter to collect the gifts. Email can be printed out or present on electrical display via mobile phone / tablet.</p>
                <p class="faq_q">Q10. Can I request for delivery of the gifts?</p>
                <p class="faq_a">Yes. As you submit your redemption claim, there will be option for either "self-collection" or "delivery". There will be a delivery charge, amount depending on the size of the item.</p>
